## 1. mbuzz — Best for Model Flexibility

**Why consider mbuzz:** HockeyStack gives you one attribution view. mbuzz lets you compare 8 models side-by-side and build custom logic for B2B.

### What mbuzz Offers

**Server-side tracking built for B2B complexity.** While HockeyStack relies on client-side tracking, mbuzz captures events on your backend—no ad blockers, no missing touches. Essential for B2B where buyer journeys span months and multiple devices.

**8 attribution models for long sales cycles.** Compare first-touch (who opened the door?), last-touch (who closed?), linear, time-decay, U-shaped, W-shaped, Markov Chain, and Shapley Value side-by-side. See how each model credits the same deal differently.

<figure class="my-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
  <%= image_tag "/images/product/attribution/model-comparison.png", alt: "mbuzz model comparison showing Linear vs Markov Chain attribution side-by-side", class: "rounded-lg border border-gray-200 shadow-sm w-full" %>
  <figcaption class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2 text-center">Compare attribution models side-by-side for B2B sales cycles</figcaption>
</figure>

**Custom attribution rules via rule editor.** Weight touchpoints by stage, channel, or engagement depth:

```ruby
# B2B-optimized: Heavy credit to first and opportunity-stage touches
model "b2b_pipeline_weighted" do
  if position == :first
    weight 0.35
  elsif stage == "opportunity_created"
    weight 0.30
  elsif channel == "direct_sales"
    weight 0.20
  else
    weight :remaining
  end
end
```

**LTV attribution for recurring revenue.** Your best first-month CAC channel might be your worst LTV channel. mbuzz tracks every renewal, upsell, and expansion back to original acquisition source—see which campaigns drive customers who renew at 130% NDR vs 80%.

